Hebr. 9:19-20
Accípiens Móyses sánguinem vitulórum, et hircórum cum aqua et lana coccínea et hyssópo: ipsum quoque librum, et omnem pópulum aspérsit, dicens: Hic sanguis testaménti, quod mandávit ad vos Deus.
Moses took the blood of calves and goats, with water, and scarlet wool and hyssop, and sprinkled both the book itself and all the people, saying: This is the blood of the testament, which God hath enjoined unto you.
